Render:

Probably take a hybrid approach in which I use a stage to manage the UI and do the rest myself.



for(Item item : placedItems) {
    if (camera.frustum.pointInFrustum(item.getVector().x, item.getVector().y, 0)) { //Only draws what can actually be seen.
            batch.draw(item.getTexture(), item.getVector().x, item.getVector().y);
    }
}
for (Ore ore : activeOre) {
    if (camera.frustum.pointInFrustum(item.getVector().x, item.getVector().y, 0)) { //Only draws what can actually be seen.
        batch.draw(ore.getTexture(), ore.getVector().x, ore.getVector().y);
    }
}



stage.draw()






Shaders:

Shader that highlights the outlines of all placed items Blue. Green or Red blue by default.

Shader that covers the ground around a placed Item in shadow.

Shaders so that special items can glow/emit light.

Shader that covers the outside of the map in shadow,

Shader that highlights the item that you are gonna place/makes it pulse white.

Shader that highlights the item you are gonna place red if not able to be placed.
